He said the agency issued “stop work notices“ to those who built on the land since 2012 but the people refused to stop building in the area. “The area is part of the eastern sector gazetted in 1994 with an order that doesn’t allow development without planning permission and statutory rights of occupancy. “Ask if they have any permits before development and our ‘X mark‘ and painting have been all over their properties advising them to stop. “We have issued stop-work notices since 2012 but they went ahead to build illegally, this is not acceptable. The area has its plan, with schools, cemeteries, markets, police station, hospital, etc, but they decided to build without regards” he said Vanguard Senator Shehu Sani and members of Akida, a pressure group within Kaduna State chapter of All Progressives Congress, APC, yesterday alleged that Governor Nasir El-Rufai has threatened to deal with them and and called on security agencies to look into the matter. June 6, 2016 In "News" The Former British Prime Minister, Mr. Tony Blair has pledged his support for Kaduna State Governor Nasir Ahmad El-Rufai's administration to deliver good governance to the people of the state. July 14, 2017 In "News" Since the return to democratic rule in 1999, Kaduna state has a governor like no other one in the last nineteen years. Governor Nasir Ahmed El Rufai, the man who, against all odds, emerged as the candidate of the All Progressive Congress, routing well established politicians in the state, in… July 14, 2018 In "News"